45451.base_text:
How should we like it were stars to burn
With a passion for us we could not return?

variants.text:
How should we like it were stars to burn
With a passion for us we could not return?

45451.base_text:
…before I die I want to see
The world that lies behind the strangeness of your eyes,
There is nothing gay or green there for my gathering, it may be,
Yet on brown fields there lies
A haunting purple bloom: is there not something in grey skies
And in grey sea?

variants.text:
…before I die I want to see
The world that lies behind the strangeness of your eyes,
There is nothing gay or green there for my gathering, it may be,
Yet on brown fields there lies
A haunting purple bloom: is there not something in grey skies
And in grey sea?

45451.base_text:
As long as the sky whirls
You will be my redemption and my doom

variants.text:
As long as the sky whirls
You will be my redemption and my doom

45451.base_text:
Some things do through our judgment pass
As through a multiplying glass.
And sometimes, if the object be too far,
We take a falling meteor for a star.

variants.text:

As through a multiplying glass.
And sometimes, if the object be too far,
We take a falling meteor for a star.

45451.base_text: “On The Road To The Sea,” Charlotte Mary Mew (1869-1928)
